    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">Copy of G M <persName role="author">Montifiore</persName>
                Letter</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>London</placeName>, <date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                    January 1847</date></p>
            <p>Gentlemen,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I beg to acknowledge the receipt of your esteemed Letter of<lb/> the
                        <date>31<hi rend="sup">st</hi> December</date> last enclosing a bill of
                Exchange for the sum of<lb/> sixty four pounds to be forwarded to the Poor of our
                Brethren in the<lb/>
                <placeName>Holy Land</placeName>. In compliance with your wish I immediately
                remitted<lb/> the amount to the Leaders of the various Congregations,
                furnishing<lb/> them with a copy of your directions with regard to the mode of
                distribution<lb/> and I requested them to forward to you an
                    <sic>acknowledgement</sic> of its<lb/> receipt, and to supply you at the same
                time with every information<lb/> with reference to the disposal of former
                remittances to the Distribution<lb/> direct from you to the worthy and highly
                respectable members of<lb/> that Committee which I would therefore beg to suggest.
                With fervent<lb/> prayers to the Almighty that you may reap in his Blessings
                the<lb/> fruits of your <sic>Benificence</sic> to our Brethren in the
                    <placeName>Holy Land</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am, gentlemen,<lb/> With sincere respect<lb/> your Obedient
                servant</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Moses Montifiore</persName>
            </p>
            <p>To, <addressee>G. B. Kursheedt &amp; Solomon J. Isaacs</addressee> Esq<hi rend="sup"
                    >res</hi>.<lb/>
                <placeName>New York</placeName></p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="underline">Note</hi>
                <hi rend="underline">by</hi>
                <hi rend="underline">the Editor</hi>. In giving the above an insertion, we beg
                leave<lb/> to state that notwithstanding the statement of our venerable friend,
                    <persName>Mr<lb/> Kursheedt</persName>, we deem the case of the Jews at
                    <placeName>Hebron</placeName> one of peculiar<lb/> hardship as they have
                suffered so much in the <add>?</add> wars which<lb/> have raged in their unfortunate
                city, and we trust that the messenger<lb/>
                <persName>Rabbi Jechal Cohen</persName> may be listened to, without our giving
                any<lb/> opinion in the administration of the <placeName>Palestine</placeName> fund
                disputes<lb/> concerning which we have long since noticed in the Orient and<lb/>
                other Jewish papers.</p>
        </body>
